  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Envelope 2013 - support to Least Developed Countries Fund (LDCF)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Least Developed Countries Fund (LDCF) was established to support a work programme to assist Least Developed Country Parties (LDCs) carry out, inter alia, the preparation and implementation of national adaptation programmes of action (NAPAs). the LDCF focuses on reducing the vulnerability of those sectors and resources that are central to development and livelihoods. These sectors include: water; agriculture and food security; health; disaster risk management and prevention; infrastructure; and fragile ecosystems. In addition, NAPA implementation projects under LDCF are designed entirely in accordance with country priorities and executed by national stakeholders, and involving active participation of vulnerable communities.</narrative>
  </description>
